DataElement.preferredName: Vector Copy Number Infused Product Known Unknown Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The indicator that describes if the vector copy number in the infused product (e.g.,human drugs; therapeutic biologics; allergenics; cells, tissue and gene therapy products; blood components and blood derivative products) was known or unknown.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The number of vector molecules present in a cell or sub-cellular location, sometimes stated as copies per diploid genome._Any form of treatment that is introduced into the body via a blood vessel, a muscle, or the spinal cord._A thing produced by or resulting from a process. EXAMPLE(S): drug, device. The FDA list of regulated products: animal and human drugs; therapeutic biologics; allergenics; cell, tissue and gene therapy products; blood components; blood derivative products; devices; and animal (pets and livestock) and human food/feed (medicated and un-medicated); cosmetics; pet treats; and dietary supplements.
